# Authoritative Facts And Docs Routing

Status: REVIEW REQUIRED

Use this file to reduce harness maintenance fan-out in {{project_name}}. Update
the authoritative owner first, then update only the surfaces that the routing
table says are affected.

## Boundary Types Covered

| Boundary Type | Default Owner |
| --- | --- |
| Local repo harness | `README.md`, `{{agent_file}}`, `docs/harness/README.md`, component inventory |
| Generated harness files | `docs/harness/manifest.json` |
| CLI/runtime behavior | Project CLI source, command tests, verification matrix |
| Existing project files | Project-owned docs, instructions, specs, scripts, workflows |
| GitHub Action or CI workflows | Workflow files and security boundary map |
| Optional workflow scaffolds | Generated workflow plus manifest metadata |
| Tests and fixtures | Project test suite, sensor registry, evidence log |
| Release/package surface | Release controls |
| Research and source records | Sources, research allowlist, source records |
| Security and privacy | Security boundary map and privacy labels |
| Platform contracts | Manifest, runtime manifests, platform source evidence |
| Docs and UX | User docs and this routing map |

## Fact Owners

| Fact Class | Authoritative Owner | Other Surfaces Should |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Purpose, platforms, runtime | README, runtime manifests, manifest | Summarize only startup-critical facts. |
| Startup and constraints | Canonical agent instruction file | Route durable detail to harness docs. |
| Components and source-of-truth docs | Component inventory | Link or summarize. |
| Verification commands and sensors | Verification matrix, sensor registry | Do not repeat every command everywhere. |
| Generated ownership and drift | Manifest | Use reports, not hand-maintained file lists. |
| Current work state and evidence | `feature_list.json`, `current-state.md`, evidence log | Use the specific file that owns the fact. Do not update state files as a bundle. |
| Security, privacy, permissions, cost | Security boundary map and privacy labels | Reference only the relevant boundary. |
| Roadmap and accepted backlog | Harness roadmap | Do not duplicate backlog lists. |

## Change-To-Docs Routing

| Change Type | Required Docs/State Updates | Usually Not Needed |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Small internal fix | No durable doc update unless the active objective or next step changes | README, manifest, roadmap, state bundle |
| CLI flag, JSON, or exit code | Usage docs, command tests, verification matrix if checks change | Broad harness README rewrite |
| Generated artifact | Template, manifest metadata, generated-content tests | Unrelated state files |
| Existing instruction enhancement | Canonical instruction file or enhance plan output, plus tests | Generated templates unless defaults change |
| GitHub Action or CI | Workflow/Action file, Action docs, security boundary if permissions change | Target docs unless guidance changes |
| Audit or report scoring | Audit/report tests and short scoring docs | README unless positioning changes |
| Platform, dependency, workflow, pin | Pin policy, manifest/platform metadata, pin evidence | Roadmap unless scope changes |
| Research or source policy | Source ledger, source records, research check evidence | CLI docs unless behavior changes |
| Release evidence | Release controls when the process changes, evidence log when evidence must be preserved | Generated templates unless guidance changes; state files unless stopping, handing off, or changing objective |

## State File Write Thresholds

Do not update state files as a bundle.

- `feature_list.json`: update only for feature status transitions, active
  objective changes, or major product evidence that must survive beyond the
  current session.
- `current-state.md`: update only when the active objective, current verified
  state, blockers, touched surfaces, or next recommended step materially
  changes.
- `docs/harness/evidence/evidence-log.md`: update only after meaningful
  verification, release evidence, audit evidence, or source review that should
  be preserved. Do not log every focused test rerun.

## Fan-Out Budgets

- 0-1 durable doc/state updates for isolated internal fixes.
- 1-3 docs/state updates for user-visible CLI, generated-content, workflow, or
  audit changes.
- More than 3 docs/state updates only for boundary, platform, security,
  release, public README, or generated-contract changes.

When a small change appears to need more updates, stop and identify the
authoritative owner before editing.
